==Introduction==
A '''Package''' groups related '''Concepts''' (See [[Help:Concept|Concept]] for more details). In most cases it corresponds to a business function supported by the Wiki.


==Definition==
<pre>
<package name={PACKAGE NAME}>
  <description>{PACKAGE DESCRIPTION}</description>

  <concept name="{CONCEPT NAME}" ...>
    ...
  </concept>
  ...
</package>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {PACKAGE NAME}
| A short name of the Package.
|-
! {PACKAGE DESCRIPTION}
| A long description of the Package.
|-
! {CONCEPT NAME}
| A short name of the Concept. See [[Help:Concept|Concept]] for more details.
|}


==Semantic database==
The Package meta-data are NOT being defined/represented in the semantic database.


==Example==
<pre>
<package name="Event Management">
  <description>Concepts required to represent information related to AV&amp;V events</description>

  <concept name="Event" plural="Events" type="Dynamic" image="Event.png" color="f9f9f9">
    <property name="Title" mandatory="true"/>
    <property name="Description" mandatory="true"/>
    <property name="Start date"/>
    <property name="End date"/>
  </concept>
</package>
</pre>


==User Interface==
Based on the Package definition the following pages are generated:
* '''Package Meta-Model Page''' (Project:Package - {PACKAGE NAME}), which displays Package meta-model information, including
** Concepts Relationships diagram
** list of package Concepts
